<subSubSection id="02C66578FFF6FFB7FF3D9AA568F37ABD" pageId="27" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF6FFB7FF3D9AA568F37ABD" blockId="27.[151,757,1761,2012]" pageId="27" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF6FFB7FF3D9AA568057B98" bold="true" box="[151,264,1761,1785]" pageId="27" pageNumber="41">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species is distinguished by its large size and the presence of a ventral umbo of clear shell material. 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF6FFB7FF3D9B6568C47A58" bold="true" box="[151,457,1825,1849]" pageId="27" pageNumber="41">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It was originally described from the Esna Shale (Late Paleocene) of the Maqfi Section by LE ROY (1953). Also, it is recorded in the Early Eocene of North Caucasus by SAPERSON &amp; JANAL (1980). It is found in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene zones of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
